Hardware testing confirms that Berlin2CD can fetch and execute a coherent
BCM NULL descriptor. Queue 6 advances, the engines return idle, and BCM
reports no error. The dHub-generated completion is visible through the
semaphore's consumer query and full condition.

Generalize the bounded descriptor submission path to follow the current
queue slot and accept the observed dHub completion semantics. Then
validate the first peripheral instruction independently of NAND command
sequencing.

Build one eight-byte CFGW descriptor using the NFC platform resource and
the configured BCM address base. Toggle bit zero of the idle controller's
NDTR0, verify that no other NAND register changed, submit a second CFGW to
restore the original timing, and validate the complete register snapshot.

Gate the test on the existing internal FIFO and NULL descriptor tests. If
a transport test fails, leave the probe-only driver bound but skip
subsequent PIO identification so a late descriptor cannot race with a
NAND command. No ND_RUN or NDCB write is issued, no NAND command or media
access occurs, and MTD registration remains disabled.

